## Why Deployment Workflow Matters

A deployment workflow defines the steps required to move software from development to production safely and consistently.

### Typical Deployment Workflow

```text
Developer
    ↓
GitHub Repository
    ↓
Code Review
    ↓
Automated Testing
    ↓
Build Process
    ↓
Staging Environment
    ↓
Production Deployment
```

### Importance of Deployment Workflows

* Ensures quality before release.
* Prevents deployment failures.
* Reduces manual errors.
* Maintains application stability.
* Improves release consistency.
* Supports large development teams.

Without a structured deployment workflow, software releases become risky and difficult to manage.

