## Problems Without Version Control

Version control systems such as Git help track and manage source code changes.

Without version control, development teams may face serious challenges.

### Problem 1: Lost Code

Developers may accidentally overwrite important work.

### Problem 2: No Change History

Teams cannot identify when or why changes were made.

### Problem 3: Difficult Collaboration

Multiple developers working on the same files can create conflicts.

### Problem 4: No Rollback Capability

Failed changes cannot be easily reverted.

### Problem 5: Deployment Confusion

Teams may deploy outdated or incomplete code.

### Example Scenario

```text
Developer A modifies Account Logic
Developer B modifies Account Logic

Without Git:
    → Changes may overwrite each other

With Git:
    → Changes are tracked and merged safely
```

### Benefits of Version Control

* Code history tracking
* Team collaboration
* Backup and recovery
* Branch management
* Release management

